	<div class="page book-page">

			<div class="content-wrap clearfix">
				<div class="book-page-book-cover">
					<img src="https://archive.org/download/swannsway_1406_librivox/swanns_way_1406.jpg" alt="book-cover-large" width="175" height="175" />

										<a href="https://archive.org/download/swannsway_1406_librivox/swanns_way_1406.jpg" class="download-cover">Download cover art</a>
					
										<a href="https://archive.org/download/swannsway_1406_librivox/swanns_way_1406.pdf" class="download-cover">Download CD case insert</a>
					
				</div>
				
				<h1>Swann's Way</h1>
				
				<p class="book-page-author"><a href="https://librivox.org/author/4253"> Marcel PROUST (1871 - 1922)</a>, translated by <a href="https://librivox.org/author/6485">C. K. SCOTT-MONCRIEFF (1889 - 1930)</a></p>
				
				<div class="description">Swann's Way is the first book in the seven-volume work <i>In Search of Lost Time</i>, or <i>Remembrance of Things Past</i>, by Marcel Proust.  It is a novel written in the form of an autobiography. Proust's most prominent work, it is popularly known for its length and the notion of involuntary memory, the most famous example being the "episode of the madeleine."  (Summary from Wikipedia)</p></div>	<!-- .description -->

				<p class="book-page-genre"><span>Genre(s):</span> General Fiction</p>

				<p class="book-page-genre"><span>Language:</span> English</p>

				
				
